<p>i have two items in my ChoiceBox like  *Fahrenheit *Celsius i want to add value to these items so that i can use switch case or if-else statements to change code. it's like if i choose Fahrenheit , it will execute code of Fahrenheit.</p>  <p>in fxml</p>  <pre><code>&lt;ChoiceBox fx:id="choice" layoutX="181.0" layoutY="14.0" prefHeight="25.0" prefWidth="119.0" value="Farhenhite" &gt; &lt;String fx:value="Farhenhite" /&gt; &lt;Separator /&gt; &lt;String fx:value="Celcius" /&gt; &lt;/ChoiceBox&gt; </code></pre>  <p>in controller</p>  <pre><code>private void handleButtonAction(ActionEvent event) {     choice.setTooltip(new Tooltip("Select the choice"));  choice.setItems(FXCollections.observableArrayList("Farhenhite", "Celcius"));       if(choice == "Farhenhite"){         int num;         String text = input.getText();         num = Integer.parseInt(text);         num = ((num - 32)*5)/9;         label.setText(Integer.toString(num) + "°" + "celcius");     } else {     }     if(choice == "Celcius"){     int num;     String text = input.getText();     num = Integer.parseInt(text);     num = ((num *  9)/5 + 32);     label.setText(Integer.toString(num) + "°" + "farhenhite");         } </code></pre>